b'Tetsujin 28-gou (2004)': b"In post-WWII Japan, Prof. Shikishima has built up Shikishima Industries to be a technological powerhouse, working on developing robots. Now Kaneda's son, Shoutarou, is about to learn the truth, and it will change him forever. \n\n(Source: ANN)"
